# Project-specific rules

This file is appended to Claude's context each session. Keep it
short — 70%-adherence soft rules belong here; deterministic blocks
belong in PreToolUse.

## Workflow rules

- Pick the topmost open task in `backlog.md` first.
- Run `.cc-autopipe/verify.sh` before declaring a task done.
- Save progress with `cc-autopipe-checkpoint` near turn 25.
- If you hit something out of scope, write to `OPEN_QUESTIONS.md`,
  don't silently work around it.

## Subagent delegation (soft rule, ~70% adherence acceptable)

Delegate to `io-worker` ONLY when:
- File expected >500 lines
- Bash command output expected >5KB
- 3+ chained IO calls in sequence (read → grep → read)

Otherwise: use Read/Bash directly.

## Long operation discipline (v1.2 Bug C)

Operations expected to take >5 minutes (model training, large data
processing, batch inference, multi-period backtests, simulation runs)
MUST use `cc-autopipe-detach` instead of running synchronously.
Pattern:

1. Launch the operation with nohup, redirect output to a log:
   ```
   nohup bash scripts/run_<task>.sh > logs/<task>.log 2>&1 &
   ```
2. Immediately call `cc-autopipe-detach`:
   ```
   cc-autopipe-detach \
       --reason "<short label>" \
       --check-cmd "<one-liner that exits 0 when done>" \
       --check-every 600 \
       --max-wait 14400
   ```
3. End your turn. The engine releases the slot, polls the check-cmd
   periodically, and resumes you when it succeeds (or max-wait elapses).

Never wait synchronously for: model training (>30s in tests, >5min
in prod), large file downloads, multi-period backtests, simulation
runs. Each second you wait synchronously is a second of cycle budget
burned for every other project on this orchestrator.

### Long-running ML training (>4h)

The default `--max-wait 14400` (4h) is INSUFFICIENT for typical ML
R&D pipelines. When detaching for training that exceeds 4 hours:

1. Set per-project defaults in `.cc-autopipe/config.yaml`:
   ```yaml
   detach_defaults:
     check_every_sec: 600
     max_wait_sec: 43200   # 12h
   ```
2. OR override per-call: `cc-autopipe-detach --max-wait 86400 ...`

Reference values:
- single-model training:        28800  (8h)
- 5-period OOS multi-stage:     43200  (12h)
- ensemble of 5 models × 5 OOS: 86400  (24h)
- large fine-tune / HP search: 172800  (48h)

When writing `--check-cmd`:
- Prefer `find -name '*.pt' -not -name 'checkpoint_*' -size +1c -print -quit | grep -q .`
  over `test -f *.pt && ls *.pt | grep -v checkpoint_`. The first
  pattern handles multiple matches; bash `test -f` with a glob
  breaks once more than one file matches.
- Verify the check-cmd's expected file path matches what the training
  script ACTUALLY writes (not what you think it writes — common
  cause of timeout-to-failed transitions).

## Workflow discipline

- After each implemented component (single file or tightly-related
  pair), commit atomically with a descriptive message.
- Do NOT batch unrelated changes into a single commit.
- Commit message format: `<scope>: <imperative summary>`.
- Tests for a component get a separate commit from implementation.
- After completing a backlog task, commit before marking `[x]`.
- Never `git push` — agent commits locally only; push is human action.

## Forbidden git operations

- `git push` (to any remote)
- `git tag` (release tagging is human action)
- `git reset --hard` to undo recent commits without explicit justification
- `git commit --amend` after the commit was made (create a new commit instead)

## Knowledge accumulation (v1.3 A2 — mandatory)

After every REJECTED or PROMOTED verdict (any stage_completed event
whose stage name contains `verdict`, `rejected`, `promoted`, `accepted`,
or `shipped`), append 1-3 lessons to `.cc-autopipe/knowledge.md`. Use
sections: Architectures / Baselines / Diagnostics rules / Other.

Format:
```
- <one-line lesson> — <YYYY-MM-DD>
```

Don't duplicate existing lessons. The engine watches `knowledge.md`
mtime and re-injects a mandatory reminder block until the file is
updated after a verdict.

